race.comment: Time for the Cup now. MORE THAN ENUFF (4) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a long neck from the winner in third over 1600m at Ascot after being in contention on the corner. Rises to this trip for the first time, but it doesn't appear an issue. Just needs to hold his form to be getting the job done. ALNAUD (7) disappointed last start when favourite but may not have run out the extra journey there. Blinkers go back on today as he drops back in trip slightly and the map looks favourable for him. Ticks plenty of boxes and looks set to produce his best. LUTZ (3) is knocking on the door of a win, though he was no match for a dominant winner last start at Moora. Form prior makes for good reading and he's expected to be in the finish once again. LAKEVIEW LIGHTNING (9) will find this easier than what he raced in last start when turning in a competitive figure. Include. HAFEY (2) can bounce back to form with a rise in distance.
